      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "the descendants of Immer, 1,052;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "41",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "the descendants of Pashhur, 1,247;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "42",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and the descendants of Harim, 1,017."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "43",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The Levites:\nthe descendants of Jeshua (through Kadmiel, through the line of Hodevah[^35]), 74."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "44",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The singers:\nthe descendants of Asaph, 148."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "45",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "The gatekeepers:\nthe descendants of Shallum,\nthe descendants of Ater,\nthe descendants of Talmon,\nthe descendants of Akkub,\nthe descendants of Hatita,\nand the descendants of Shobai,\n138 in all."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "46",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "The temple servants:[^36]\nthe descendants of Ziha,\nthe descendants of Hasupha,\nthe descendants of Tabbaoth,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "47",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "the descendants of Keros,\nthe descendants of Sia,[^37]\nthe descendants of Padon,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "48",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "the descendants of Lebanah,\nthe descendants of Hagabah,\nthe descendants of Shalmai,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "49",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "the descendants of Hanan,\nthe descendants of Giddel,\nthe descendants of Gahar,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "50",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "the descendants of Reaiah,\nthe descendants of Rezin,\nthe descendants of Nekoda,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "51",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "the descendants of Gazzam,\nthe descendants of Uzza,\nthe descendants of Paseah,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "52",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "the descendants of Besai,\nthe descendants of Meunim,\nthe descendants of Nephushesim,[^38]"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "53",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "the descendants of Bakbuk,\nthe descendants of Hakupha,\nthe descendants of Harhur,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "54",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "the descendants of Bazlith,[^39]\nthe descendants of Mehida,\nthe descendants of Harsha,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "55",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "the descendants of Barkos,\nthe descendants of Sisera,\nthe descendants of Temah,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "56",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "the descendants of Neziah,\nand the descendants of Hatipha."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "57",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "The descendants of the servants of Solomon:\nthe descendants of Sotai,\nthe descendants of Sophereth,\nthe descendants of Perida,[^40]"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "58",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "the descendants of Jaala,\nthe descendants of Darkon,\nthe descendants of Giddel,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "59",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "the descendants of Shephatiah,\nthe descendants of Hattil,\nthe descendants of Pochereth-hazzebaim,\nand the descendants of Amon.[^41]"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "60",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "census/list",
          "text": "The temple servants and descendants of the servants of Solomon numbered 392 in all."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "61",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The following came up from Tel-melah, Tel-harsha, Cherub, Addon,[^42] and Immer, but could not prove that their families were descended from Israel:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "62",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "the descendants of Delaiah,\nthe descendants of Tobiah,\nand the descendants of Nekoda,\n642 in all."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "63",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "And from among the priests: the descendants of Hobaiah,\nthe descendants of Hakkoz,\nand the descendants of Barzillai (who had married a daughter of Barzillai the Gileadite and was called by their name)."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "64",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "law",
          "text": "These men searched for their family records, but they could not find them and so were excluded from the priesthood as unclean."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "65",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The governor ordered them not to eat the most holy things until there was a priest to consult the Urim and Thummim.[^43]"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "66",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The whole assembly numbered 42,360,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "67",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "in addition to their 7,337 menservants and maidservants, as well as their 245 male and female singers."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "68",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "They had 736 horses, 245 mules,[^44]"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "69",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "435 camels, and 6,720 donkeys."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Offerings by the Exiles"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "70",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Some of the heads of the families contributed to the project. The governor gave to the treasury 1,000 darics of gold,[^45]50 bowls, and 530 priestly garments."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "71",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And some of the heads of the families gave to the treasury for the project 20,000 darics of gold[^46] and 2,200 minas of silver.[^47]"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "72",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The rest of the people gave a total of 20,000 darics of gold, 2,000 minas of silver,[^48] and 67 priestly garments."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "73",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "So the priests, Levites, gatekeepers, singers, and temple servants, along with some of the people and the rest of the Israelites, settled in their own towns. And by the seventh month the Israelites had settled in their towns."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}